The office has a relatively simple air conditioning system - a single ceiling mounted inlet in each room, with an extraction grille in the ceiling above the main entrance door. The system was included in the model since it increases the movement of air from one room to another, and therefore the spread of contaminants and aerosols.

Sample results are provided in the figures below, showing a sneeze followed by the spread of water droplets through the office space as a consequence of the air movement induced by the HVAC system. As can be seen in Figures 3-6, someone walking into the office through the main entrance door could be exposed to quite a few droplets for this specific case.

